{{RecommendedAudioNest|audio={{Audio|file=Silksong OST - Chapel - Orion.mp3|round=yes|volume=0.6|align=center}}}}

{{Borderimage|image=174-1.webp|width=340px|align=center|caption=Don't Slip.}}


An ascending complex of play structures that extends far above the ground, contained within a chapel constantly lit up by warm rays of sunlight. This is the description of Level 174, also known as the '''Citadel of Jablon'''; the 175<sup>th</sup> level of the backrooms.

The level itself is comprised of multiple pathways, staircases and rope bridges connected to steel framing; concealed by sheets of vinyl fabric that vary in color. It is important to note that the vinyl coating is impossible to break through or damage intentionally, with most bladed weapons usually breaking upon contact with it. The fabric may also start bulging at random with scuttling noises being heard as well. Upon adknowldgement of the sight, any wanderer will begin to crave apples; further inducing their intent to climb towards the top.

While exploring the level one may also find shattered apples across the floor, these apples supposedly fall down from the tree at the top of the chapel; breaking open due to the sheer height of the fall. The fruits themselves take on a blue or orange skin with a red inside that reportedly smells like caramel, however the taste is described similarly to a rag used to clean up blood and urine. Once consumed, the wanderer will suddenly begin to experience severe insanity before passing out and waking up back in [[Level 177]]; with no memory of Level 174 whatsoever. This effect remains until the wanderer encounters Level 174 again through [[Level 177]] or any other exits into the level.

Some structures within Level 174 may also be covered with tree branches and vines, supposedly from the trees within the outside area of [[Level 177]] entering the structure similarly to how [[Level 338]]'s trees act. The branches can cause structural instability within Level 174, leading to wanderers falling off the structures and potentially resulting in death. The branches may also block off areas depending on their size, preventing further ascension.

{{Borderimage|image=174-3.jpg|width=340px|align=center|caption=Preceding the fall.}}

Church windows, constructed from stained glass; can be found in abundance while ascending Level 174. The church windows usually display religous artwork, depicting the tale of Adam and Eve; in high detail and in explicit fashion. The windows structurally appear to be significantly weaker than normal glass, even a slight tap causes the window to shatter entirely, revealing the exterior of [[Level 177]] behind it. The artwork within the windows may also move suddenly on occasions, the movement being described as a twitching motion; viewing the windows during this event causes the wanderer to experience panic attacks and mental breakdowns for reasons unknown.

Religious items may also be found scattered about Level 174, specifically in the upper regions due to their close proximity to the apple tree. These items include:

*White mantles with golden accents, usually featuring a golden cross in the middle
*Wooden crucifixes, often damaged or shattered
*Golden polearms embedded with christian symbols
*Items related to the zodiac calendar
*Copies of the Holy Bible, usually the latest version
*Talisman sheets
*Goblets filled with [[Object 12|Liquid Pain]]

Any interaction with these items will instantly instate the Level 174 Effect upon the target.

{{Imagebox|file=174-1.webp|text= I never really prayed to God, or at least I thought so.


When I entered this level, I knew something was off instantly. I kept feeling this overarching demonic presence coming from somewhere up above, not really sure what it was but I knew that leaving this level was the safest option out of all of them I had. I instantly ran for the wooden doors behind me, when I opened the door; I was in this [[Level 177|weird forest with holes in the trees]]. It was dark out so I lit the lantern I prepared, that set off an entity nearby, it was skinless and had things protruding through its body, every movement came with a loud cracking noise. It was enough to send me back into the chapel, when I looked back; the entity was gone. I was back in the chapel with no way out, so hopeless me decided to climb up the structure.}}

==The Level 174 effect==

The Level 174 Effect, also known as the '''Lust of Jablon'''; is a phenomenon exclusive to Level 174. The effect is activated when viewing the "Bugs" or interacting with any religious objects within Level 174. Once activated, the victim will begin to traverse Level 174 to reach the apple tree located at the highest point of the level, regardless of any hazards present. At a certain point within the climb, the wanderer will feel a pushing motion that causes them to fall back down to the start of the level; causing them to suffer fatal injuries that usually lead into death. However if a wanderer doesn't perish while doing so, they will start climbing the level again, regardless of any mobility hindering injuries sustained from the fall; eventually dying from their injuries in a randomised amount of time.

==Entities==
No entities can exist within Level 174 due to its cover under [[Phenomenon 15]]

==Entrances and Exits==

===Entrances===
*Finding a chapel deep within the forest of [[Level 177|Hanging Sparrow]] leads here.
*Entering through a pair of church doors within [[Level 257|Scene 75: They're still alive out there, somewhere.]] can lead here, although these doors are extremley rare to come across.
*Interacting with a cross inside the [[Level 197|Closing Hypermarket]] can lead here.
*[[Level Fun]] may suddenly transform into this level at random.
===Exits===
*Supposedly, eating a fruit from the apple tree leads into [[Level 666|Aint All Blood Red]] though it most likely leads to a [[Boundless Torturer|worse punishment]].
*Walking outside the chapel leads back to [[Level 177|Hanging Sparrow]]
*<s>Although unconfirmed, reportedly noclipping during the Lust of Jablon leads to [[Level 399|Neon Paradise]]</s> [[Level 959|DO NOT ATTEMPT]]
*Interacting with any items related to one's past leads to the [[Level 237|Indoor Graveyard]]
*Falling down a deep chasm located somewhere in the upper areas leads into [[Level 164|Structures in The Dark]].
*Interacting with spoiled food items teleports the wanderer to [[Level 72|The Worm in The Fruit]]
